<subSubSection pageId="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,258,895]" pageId="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,690,715]" pageId="7">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Large, wingless, distinctly two-colored beetle, characterized by presence of sub-quadrate pronotum with dentiform basal angles, interval 
<number box="[566,580,727,751]" pageId="7" value="3.0">3</number>
with three foveolate setiferous punctures, apical end of stria 
<number box="[1260,1274,727,750]" pageId="7" value="7.0">7</number>
with four-five small setiferous punctures, sternum VII in male strongly depressed at sides and apical part, with stout medial, longitudinal projection and fine transverse subapical sulcus broken at carina (sternum VII in female with slight medial projection and fine transverse subapical sulcus broken at middle), median lobe of aedeagus stout, with apex clearly bent to right at dorsal aspect.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
